      "writtenOn": "2026-06-08T06:40:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "@ed@tanous.net This guard is intentional and not an async misunderstanding. It is a fail-fast check for synchronous errors set by the immediately preceding helper. If that helper has already set a non-OK response, we return immediately to avoid continuing PATCH processing and creating mixed response behavior. You are correct that this check does not capture errors that arrive later from async callbacks; those are handled in the callback paths.",
      "parentUuid": "b66ea2f3_95d823c9",
      "revId": "6be53eebeb21d1a93239ffa44efb93c0253a5ef2",
